OL,6,FThe prosecution claims he remained in
OL,7,Fhis car, but was the ringleader of the
OL,8,Frobbery.
OL,10,FAssisted by an interpreter, Mr Khan,
OL,11,F75, told the jury he had used
OL,12,FUniversal Express to transfer money to
OL,13,FPakistan but had "never set foot" in
OL,14,Fthe premises.
OL,16,FHe said the business's owner, Mohammad
OL,17,FYousaf had "lost his trust" after
OL,18,F#12,000 he gave him to send to
OL,19,FPakistan was not transferred.
